SessionToken.Description:
Specifies the session token for the current command. A session token is constant throughout the life of the session.
To obtain a session token, run the StartSession command. This SessionToken is required for every subsequent command that is issued during the current session.

StartSession.Description: Command to start a new session. A session token is obtained as part of the response.

StartTransaction.Description: Command to start a new transaction.

EndSession.Description: Command to end the current session.

CommitTransaction.Description: Command to commit the specified transaction.

AbortTransaction.Description: Command to abort the current transaction.

ExecuteStatement.Description: Command to execute a statement in the specified transaction.
